Meningococcal disease in Singapore, Indonesia, Iran and Morocco
---------------------------------------------------------------
_Neisseria meningitidis_ serogroup W135 has been identified in the majority
of serogrouped confirmed cases associated with international travel and
reported previously [by WHO on 27 April; 26 April; 20 April; 11 April.
Laboratory confirmation is underway for new notifications received from the
following countries:
Singapore: Four cases;
Indonesia: Fourteen cases, including 6 deaths, with laboratory confirmation
of _N. meningitidis_ serogroup B in 1 case;
Iran: Two cases;
Morocco: Three cases, with laboratory confirmation of 1 case of _N.
meningitidis_ serogroup W135 and 1 case of serogroup C.
WHO is actively monitoring the situation and requesting countries to send
specimens to WHO Collaborating Centres for Meningococcal Infections so that
the strains can be fully identified and traced. The Centres are:
Institut de Medecine Tropicale du Service de Sante des Armees
